      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T03:02:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: Bool args like this are notoriously hard to understand when reading code. There are two approaches I like to make it easier to read:\n1. Add an enum for the possibilities. This is particularly easy in Go:\ntype getTestDigestsExpsKeysOnly bool\nconst getEntities getTestDigestsExpsKeysOnly \u003d false\nconst getKeysOnly getTestDigestsExpsKeysOnly \u003d true\n\n2. Add a comment to each call site, e.g.:\n_, expColl, err :\u003d c.getTestDigestExps(nil, parentKey, /* keysOnly */ false)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 198,
        "startChar": 58,
        "endLine": 198,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "3250a5301822415905daa114c9ac5d64d46c7a64",
